---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../../../../components/Callout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Client Feedback" description="Collect feedback on FactFeed, create tickets, iterate, then get sign-off.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Client Feedback</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">In Project 1, the client was Ken — a landscaper reviewing his business site. For FactFeed, imagine you're showing the app to your team lead or an early user. Same process: show, collect feedback, turn it into tickets, iterate.</p>

  <h2 class="mb-4">The reviewer's feedback</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You send the staging URL to your team lead. They open it on their laptop and phone, click around for a few minutes, and come back with notes:</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm mb-3"><strong>From team lead:</strong></p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2">"Nice work, it's functional. Three things I noticed:</p>
    <ol class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 mb-2">
      <li>The loading spinner is almost invisible on the white card background — I wasn't sure if it was loading or broken.</li>
      <li>If I click 'Next Fact' really fast, it seems to queue up multiple requests. Can you debounce that or disable the button while loading?</li>
      <li>It would be nice to see when each fact was fetched — even just a small timestamp or 'fetched 2 hours ago' label.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Otherwise, ready to go."</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">Turn feedback into tickets</h2>
  <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-bold text-primary bg-primary-bg px-2 py-1 rounded">CF-1</span>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Make loading spinner visible on white background</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Why:</strong> Spinner is nearly invisible against the card's white background.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-1"><strong>Acceptance criteria:</strong></p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
        <li>Spinner uses the primary blue colour (#2563EB), not a light grey</li>
        <li>Spinner is at least 24px and clearly visible on white</li>
        <li>Loading state is unmistakably different from the success state</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-bold text-primary bg-primary-bg px-2 py-1 rounded">CF-2</span>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Prevent rapid-fire requests on "Next Fact"</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Why:</strong> Clicking rapidly queues multiple API requests.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-1"><strong>Acceptance criteria:</strong></p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
        <li>"Next Fact" button is disabled while a request is in flight</li>
        <li>Button shows a disabled visual state (opacity 0.5, cursor not-allowed)</li>
        <li>Button re-enables after the response arrives (success or error)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-bold text-primary bg-primary-bg px-2 py-1 rounded">CF-3</span>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Show when the fact was fetched</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Why:</strong> User wants to know how fresh the facts are.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-1"><strong>Acceptance criteria:</strong></p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
        <li>Display a relative timestamp below the source (e.g. "fetched 2 hours ago")</li>
        <li>Uses the <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">created_at</code> field from the API response</li>
        <li>Styled in secondary text colour, same size as source label</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">Fix them</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Same loop. Direct Claude with the three tickets:</p>
  <CodeBlock copy>{`Fix three client feedback items:

CF-1: Make the loading spinner visible — use primary blue (#2563EB), at least 24px.
CF-2: Disable "Next Fact" button while a request is in flight. Re-enable on response.
CF-3: Show a relative timestamp ("fetched 2 hours ago") below the source, using created_at from the API.`}</CodeBlock>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4 mb-4">Verify each fix, merge, redeploy to the staging URL. Show the reviewer again. They confirm all three are fixed.</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Notice the pattern:</strong> feedback on a utility app is different from a business site. It's about interaction quality — loading states, race conditions, data freshness — not copy or layout. The process is the same.</p>
  </Callout>
</DocsLayout>
